\v 49 \w When|strong="H1121"\w* \w Shaul|strong="H7586"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w Baal-Hanan|strong="H1177"\w*, \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Acbor|strong="H5907"\w*, \w took|strong="H4191"\w* \w over|strong="H4427"\w* \w as|strong="H8478"\w* \w king|strong="H4427"\w*.
\v 50 When \w Baal-Hanan|strong="H1177"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w Hadad|strong="H1908"\w* \w took|strong="H4191"\w* \w over|strong="H4427"\w* \w as|strong="H8478"\w* \w king|strong="H4427"\w*. \w The|strong="H8478"\w* \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w of|strong="H1323"\w* \w his|strong="H8478"\w* \w city|strong="H5892"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w Pau|strong="H6464"\w*.\f + \fr 1:50 \ft In most Hebrew manuscripts “Pai,” but some Hebrew and Septuagint manuscripts have “Pau.” See \xt Genesis 36:39\xt*\ft .\f* \w The|strong="H8478"\w* \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w of|strong="H1323"\w* \w his|strong="H8478"\w* wife \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w Mehetabel|strong="H4105"\w*, \w daughter|strong="H1323"\w* \w of|strong="H1323"\w* \w Matred|strong="H4308"\w*, \w the|strong="H8478"\w* \w daughter|strong="H1323"\w* \w of|strong="H1323"\w* Me-Zahab.
\v 51 \w Then|strong="H1961"\w* \w Hadad|strong="H1908"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*. \w The|strong="H1961"\w* chiefs \w of|strong="H4191"\w* Edom\f + \fr 1:51 \ft The name listing changes from kings to chiefs since after this time Edom was under the rule of Israel and so did not have its own king.\f* \w were|strong="H1961"\w*: \w Timna|strong="H8555"\w*, \w Alvah|strong="H5933"\w*, \w Jetheth|strong="H3509"\w*,
