\p 
\v 31 These \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* musicians David \w appointed|strong="H1121"\w* \w to|strong="H1121"\w* direct \w the|strong="H1121"\w* music \w in|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* house \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* Lord once \w the|strong="H1121"\w* Ark \w had|strong="H1121"\w* been placed there.
\v 32 They led out \w in|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* music \w and|strong="H1121"\w* singing before \w the|strong="H1121"\w* Tabernacle, \w the|strong="H1121"\w* Tent \w of|strong="H1121"\w* Meeting, until Solomon built \w the|strong="H1121"\w* Lord's Temple \w in|strong="H1121"\w* Jerusalem. They served following \w the|strong="H1121"\w* regulations they \w had|strong="H1121"\w* been given.
\p 
\v 33 Here \w are|strong="H1004"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w men|strong="H3605"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* served, together \w with|strong="H1004"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* sons: \w From|strong="H3881"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Kohathites: Heman, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* singer, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* son \w of|strong="H1004"\w* Joel, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* son \w of|strong="H1004"\w* Samuel,
